		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">Investigation of formal techniques that support the design of System-on-Chip (SOC) architectures, in particular on-chip interconnects. SOCs integrate a number of co-operating modules on a single chip; typically dedicated for a specific domain, e.g. multimedia processing. These modules are linked via a high-speed processing with real time communication and provide a challenging application. A variety of formal approaches to modelling, analysis and verification of general hardware and communication systems exits, their practical use of formal techniques by integrating different approaches in a uniform verification environment specialised to support SOC design. The first project stage develops a modelling framework that can be used to represent the functional behaviour of a SOC, as well as its performance analysis. The system will be tested using a formal model of a multimedia SOC. A CCS/CSP-based modelling language and techniques based on the observational behaviour paradigm are expected to be suitable.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
